From 4d5495d48b63e48ab2cbde27d75d58f85f72b1e2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Keane (via Claude)" <keane@cybershield.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 13:45:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] security: move quiz answer validation server-side
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Rebased onto latest master (resultId-based navigation / QuizAttemptDao).

- Add Cloud Functions validateAnswer / validateAnswersBatch that grade
  answers against a server-only answerKeys collection (Admin SDK), guarded
  by App Check + auth.
- Remove correctIndex/explanation from the client-facing Question model
  and from Firestore question docs (migrated to answerKeys via
  functions/src/scripts/migrateAnswerKeys.ts).
- Firestore rules: block all client writes to quizResults and all client
  read/write to answerKeys — grading + persistence now only happen via
  the Admin SDK inside the Cloud Functions.
- Online: QuizViewModel calls validateAnswer immediately for instant
  correct/incorrect feedback, using only the server's verdict.
- Offline: answers are cached locally (selectedIndex only, no isCorrect)
  and graded later by SyncQuizResultsWorker via validateAnswersBatch once
  connectivity returns; the persisted QuizAttempt (and QuizResultScreen)
  are marked provisional and XP/badge/certificate awarding is deferred
  until every answer is graded.
- QuizAttemptEntity gains a provisional column so a reloaded result
  screen still reflects the right state.
- Room schema (bumped to version 7): quiz_results gains
  questionId/selectedIndex/explanation, isCorrect is now nullable pending
  server grading.
- Test suite updated: QuizViewModelTest, QuizRepositoryImplTest,
  FirestoreQuizDataSourceTest, QuizDaoTest, QuizResultDaoTest,
  FakeQuizRepository, plus new FunctionsQuizDataSourceTest.
